<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-20T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-20T20:00:00-05:00" n="218" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">No. 218</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">840B.062/4–1851: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Legation in Iceland</gloss>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d218fn1">
                                    <persName corresp="#p_BKA1">Byrns</persName> (<gloss target="#t_BNA1">BNA</gloss>) drafted and initialed for the
                                    Secretary.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret   priority</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-20T20:00:00-05:00">April
                                        20, 1951—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>201. In order reply <gloss target="#t_Legtel1">Legtel</gloss> 210 Apr
                                    18<note n="2" xml:id="d218fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> we need your and <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> further views re: <list>
                                    <label>1.</label>
                                    <item>Possibility that arrival of troops before May 18 might
                                        precipitate strike earlier than scheduled.</item>
                                    <label>2.</label>
                                    <item>Feeling of Govt, labor, and public which wld indicate any
                                        possibility avoiding strike and if not, its seriousness,
                                        possible duration, difficulties in way of settlement.</item>
                                    <label>3.</label>
                                    <item>Possibility signing agreement as soon possible, and then
                                        keeping it secret for period long enough permit later entry
                                        of troops, say June. Wld this jeopardize Agreement if Govt
                                        thinks Althing action necessary?</item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                            <p>Destroyers <hi rend="italic">Brownson</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Meredith</hi> scheduled visit Reykjavik Apr 28–May 1. If troops
                                not available wld lay-over or somewhat later arrival these ships be
                                useful and permit announcement agreement? Both above queries
                                exploratory only as no firm assurance can yet be given that
                                destroyers cld delay their schedule, and no decision yet made that
                                this course advisable.</p>
                            <p>Assume <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> desires coincident
                                arrival troops and announcement agreement order to avoid public
                                disturbances. Has he any other reasons? Has he considered propaganda
                                value to Soviet of arrival coincident with announcement, giving
                                appearance whole procedure rigged by two Govts fearing Ice public
                                reaction.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>